<SUBJECT>R -- United States Transportation Command (USTRANSCOM) Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff (CJCS) Exercise Program
<SOLNBR>FA445203R0008
<CONTACT>Nancy Jurke, Contracting Officer, Phone (618) 256-9963, Fax (618) 256-5724, Email Nancy.Jurke@scott.af.mil - Lee White, Contract Specialist, Phone 618 256 9952, Fax 618 256 3091, Email leeann.white@scott.af.mil
<DESC>The AMC Contracting Flight anticipates issuance of a solicitation on a full and open competitive basis for support of the USTRANSCOM Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff (CJCS) Exercise Program at Scott AFB, IL and other worldwide locations.  This exercise program provides collective training in wartime tasks, and assessments of the command’s ability to meet those requirements.  The contractor shall provide support for the following requirements:  1) perform an analysis of current collective training status, providing a report which recommends Joint Mission-Essential Tasks (JMETs) to be trained;  2) prepare for each exercise an Exercise Management Plan (EMP) which describes the contractor’s approach;  3) develop a specific Concept of Operations (CONOPS);  4) generate an Exercise Directive (EXDIR) that tasks training participants;  5) develop a Master Scenario Events List (MSEL) which is directly linked to JMET training objectives;  6) create implementer documents which initiate exercise events;  7) provide event control, process expertise, and observation during exercises;  8) after exercises, prepare an observation report which contains observations/lessons learned/issues (OLIs) for input into the Remedial Action Program;  9) develop an After Action Report (AAR) and Joint After Action Report (JAAR) which analyze OLIs against Joint Training Plan standards to assess the command’s ability to meet wartime taskings.  The anticipated period of performance will be one year with four one-year option periods.  The NAICS code is 541611.  Anticipated issuance date is 1 Jun 03.  No hard copies of this solicitation will be issued. The solicitation may be downloaded from the Federal Business Opportunities (FedBizOpps) website at http://www.eps.gov.  All comments should be addressed Ms Nancy Jurke, Contracting Officer (618) 256-9963, e-mail nancy.jurke@scott.af.mil, or Ms. Lee Ann White, Contracting Specialist, (618) 256-9952, FAX (618) 256-5724, e-mail leeann.white@scott.af.mil.
